The paper deals with a graph optimization problem and presents an approximation algorithm for it. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories related to algorithms and optimization, such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), and cs.CG (computational geometry). Additionally, the problem involves graph cuts, which is a well-studied topic in theoretical computer science and could place the paper in sub-categories such as cs.GT (graph theory) and cs.CC (computational complexity).
